Install TLP
	sudo apt-get install tlp


	tlp => apply laptop power saving settings
	tlp-stat => displays all power saving settings
	tlp-pcilist => displays PCI(e) device data
	tlp-usblist => for viewing USB devices data

Check if it running under SystemD using
	sudo systemctl status tlp


	sudo tlp start
	sudo tlp-stat (show all power settings)
	sudo tlp-stat -s (show system information)
	sudo tlp-stat -c (show configuration)
	sudo tlp-stat -b (show battery information)
	sudo tlp-stat -p (show processor data)
	sudo tlp-stat -w (show warning)
	sudo tlp-stat -t (show temperature)
